Class 06

Alerts:
Alert is a pop up message.
Alerts take a complete focus of our main page that we are on.
We cannot proceed further until it is handle;
3 type of Alert;
1. Web Based alerts/HTML Alerts-we can simply inspect and perform needed actions
2.Javascript Alert/browser alert--we can handle these alerts by using switchTo method
we cannot inspect
3.windows based alert-- we cannot handle witch selenium

Types of JS alerts:
1.Simple alert-click ok;
2.conformation alert-ether cancel or click ok;
3.prom alert- ether the text and then click ok or cancel

to handle JS alerts we only have 4 methods;
1.accept()-click ok
2.dismiss()-click on cancel;
3.getText()
4.sendKeys()

Frame is a separate independent window in our webpage
Frame allows devs to represent


3 ways to interact or to switch to a frame
1.by index
2.by name or id
3.by webelements


in alert-switch to an alert manually and switch back automaticlly
in frames-switch to frame manually and switch back to the main page manually

Interview Question;
How do you handle Alerts in Selenium;
We handle Alerts by using Alert interface;














